  "summary": "Malicious code in home-sections-web-ui (npm)",
  "details": "Dependency-confusion package at version 99.9.9 that declares a dependency \"ltidisafe\" pointing to an external tarball hosted at hxxps://storage[.]googleapis[.]com/lscunpentest/pack_ux_foundry[.]tgz. The package itself is a minimal stub (397 bytes, index.js contains only a console.log). The actual payload is delivered from the external GCS-hosted tarball when npm install resolves the dependency. The package has no repository, no lifecycle hooks, and its description is a nonsensical string (\"lspodcc\").",
